        <h2>The Wilson Room</h2><a name="the-wilson-room"></a><p>The Norman W. and Glenville Starr Wilson Room, located separately from the Special
          Collections &amp; Archives area in The Valley Library, is the result of a gift of books,
          art, and furnishings provided by Norman W. Wilson, retired Professor of English at
          the University. More information available in <a href="coll/wilson/index.html">The Wilson Room</a> collection.
        </p>
        <p>
        <div class="teifigure" style="width: 320px;"><a href="<?php echo($_ARCHON->PublicInterface->ImagePath); ?>/facilities-wilsonroom1-large.jpg"><img src="<?php echo($_ARCHON->PublicInterface->ImagePath); ?>/facilities-wilsonroom1.jpg" width="320" height="240" alt="The Wilson Room" title="The Wilson Room" /></a><br /><span class="caption-head">The Wilson Room</span><br /><span class="caption-desc">Wilson and his late wife, Glenville, spent many years traveling in England and in
                           the Pacific Northwest. During their travels, they capitalized on their ever-increasing
                           interest in 18th and 19th century British history, collecting antiques, artifacts,
                           and volumes reminiscent of the period.</span></div>
        <div class="teifigure" style="width: 320px;"><a href="<?php echo($_ARCHON->PublicInterface->ImagePath); ?>/facilities-wilsonroom2-large.jpg"><img src="<?php echo($_ARCHON->PublicInterface->ImagePath); ?>/facilities-wilsonroom2.jpg" width="320" height="240" alt="The Wilson Room" title="The Wilson Room" /></a><br /><span class="caption-head">The Wilson Room</span><br /><span class="caption-desc">In 1993, Wilson asked the Oregon State University Libraries if it might be interested
                           in receiving a portion of his collection for use by students and scholars who would
                           study the period reflected by his holdings.</span></div><br style="clear: both;" /></p>
        <p>
